<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>And by the time anyone gets such an improved Manaburn these encounters should be trivial.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
After Manaburn had been out for awhile there started to be a trend of higher level content suddenly being killed by guilds that had previously been unable to even scathe the hps of these mobs. What was happening was the lower level guilds were collecting a group of wizards who had MB and using them to great advantage on these targets. When they &quot;nerfed&quot; manaburn suddenly very many of these guilds were no longer able to drop these very same targets they were mowing down weeks earlier. The game should not be won on the skill of a single class. I would not like to see a guild roaming the Plane of Fire because they had 8 people who were able to play an extrioardinary amount of time. /shrug<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Rallos Zek is not a 6 second fight. The fact that you can do 19500 damage in 6 seconds doesn't really matter all that much.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Anyone who has succesfully beaten the RZ encounter will most likely agree with me when I say 6 seconds can mean win or lose on that event. I know that on one of our tries he was at 2 percent and we wiped. 6 more seconds would have given us the victory.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I'm going to call you on this one. Please show me how it's possible to regain enough mana after a MB to nuke as normal and ride the edge of aggro on the encounter. You will not have that much mana.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I also am in this situation so I can verify and support this claim. Our mana regen can be very sick if we get the right AA, gear and auxillary support.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I can already say that it's not normal for a bard to be playing a mana regen song on a fight which, as you called it, is a DPS race.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This brings me back to my very first question on your experience with PoP encounters. It can be very normal for a bard to be dedicated to playing Manasong/Rizlona's for a wizard group. No other class is outdamaging a wizard who is doing a good job of aggro control in this situation. No DPS is lost if there are enough bards present to support the other classes either.<br>
<br>
I stand by the observation that an improved manaburn would ruin the present game. <br>
